    • Uses of Entity in Character

      Subclasses of Entity in Character 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AttributeCharacter
      Abstract class that determines what makes a character possess attributes, such as speed.
      class  Character
      Abstract class that determines what makes an entity a character in the game.
      class  CivilianCharacter
      A CivilianCharacter is a NPC with carries a certain amount of quests.
      class  EnemyCharacter
      The basic enemy in the game.
      class  PlayerCharacter
      The user-controlled player in the game.
      class  ShopCharacter
      A shop character can be used to purchase items from.

    • Uses of Entity in Item

      Subclasses of Entity in Item 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ArmorItem
      ArmorItems extends Item and has a instance variabel for a defence rating.
      class  Item
      Abstract class for all Items in the game.
      class  LifeItem
      LifeItem extends Item and gives life (potion or a heart).
      class  MoneyItem
      MoneyItem extends Item and has a instance variabel for money value.
      class  WeaponItem
      WeaponItem extends Item and has two instance variables for a attack damage and a attack speed.

    • Uses of Entity in World

      Subclasses of Entity in World 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  BlockTile
      This class checks if the tile is a blocktile, if it's a blocktile the characters can't walk on the specific tile.
      class  DoorTile
      This class keeps track of which doors will be active when the respective map is used, leaving the rest up to its superclass, Tile.
      class  Tile
      This class gives its superclass Entity information about all the Tiles position and id number
